  "summary": "## Summary: Gmail OAuth Connect Flow\n\n### Changes Implemented\n- Created Gmail OAuth initiation route (`GET /api/gmail/oauth?action=connect` redirects to Google OAuth consent screen, `GET /api/gmail/oauth` returns connection status, `DELETE /api/gmail/oauth` disconnects)\n- Created Gmail OAuth callback route (`GET /api/gmail/oauth/callback` exchanges auth code for tokens, fetches user email, auto-sets up Gmail Watch via Pub/Sub)\n- Updated `GmailWatchManager` component to use a one-click \"Connect Gmail\" OAuth button instead of a manual form requiring tokens\n- Added URL parameter handling for `gmail_connected` and `gmail_error` (same pattern as Outlook/Zoom)\n- Replaced the verbose 6-step manual Pub/Sub setup instructions with a concise description of the OAuth flow\n- Kept the Apps Script alternative as a fallback option for users who prefer polling\n- Removed unused `handleStop` function and manual form state (`setupForm`, `showSetup`)\n\n### Files Modified\n- `app/api/gmail/oauth/route.ts` (new) ‚Äî Gmail OAuth initiation + status + disconnect\n- `app/api/gmail/oauth/callback/route.ts` (new) ‚Äî OAuth callback with token exchange + auto watch setup\n- `app/(app)/admin/integrations/IntegrationsClient.tsx` ‚Äî Replaced manual Gmail form with OAuth connect button, simplified instructions\n\n### Notes for Developer\n- Requires 3 environment variables in `.env.local`:\n  - `GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID` ‚Äî from Google Cloud Console OAuth 2.0 credentials\n  - `GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET` ‚Äî from Google Cloud Console OAuth 2.0 credentials\n  - `GOOGLE_PUBSUB_TOPIC` ‚Äî e.g. `projects/my-project/topics/gmail-inbound`\n- The Google Cloud OAuth consent screen must have `http://localhost:3000/api/gmail/oauth/callback` (or your production domain) as an authorized redirect URI\n- Gmail API and Pub/Sub API must be enabled in the Google Cloud project\n- The OAuth flow requests `gmail.readonly` and `email` scopes\n- Watch subscriptions expire after 7 days ‚Äî use the \"Renew Watch\" button in the UI\n- TypeScript compiles cleanly with no errors"
}